## Repository layout

```
{{repo_name}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                      ← you are here
├── docs/
│   └── PLAN.md                    ← canonical WP plan
├── resources/                     ← upstream references (do not modify)
├── {{src_dir}}/                   ← {{one-line description}}
├── {{data_dir}}/                  ← generated by scripts/
├── scripts/                       ← data-extraction / build scripts
├── tests/
└── {{build_file}}
```

`resources/` holds read-only upstream material (papers, reference
implementations, external data dictionaries) that the project builds on
but does not modify. `scripts/` holds committed scripts that transform
`resources/` (and other inputs) into derived data under `{{data_dir}}/`.
If the project has no external materials, delete the `resources/` line.

## Execution model

- One Claude session per WP. For any prompt of the form *"implement
  WPx"*, *"work on WPx"*, or *"continue with WPx"*, invoke the
  `wp-workflow` skill with `implement <WPx>`. **Do not begin
  implementation before `ExitPlanMode` approval on a per-WP plan** —
  `docs/PLAN.md` says what each WP is; the per-WP plan written at the
  start of the session says how to do it in this repo right now.
- **The user owns version control.** Never run `git add`, `git commit`,
  `git push`, `git rm`, `git reset`, `git stash`, or any other mutating
  git command, and never propose to. Summarise what changed in plain
  text and let the user commit. Read-only git is fine.
- **Stay inside this repository.** Do not edit files outside the repo
  without an explicit instruction in the current session.
- Each WP ends by updating this file (completed-WPs list below) and, if
  needed, `docs/PLAN.md`.
- When `docs/PLAN.md` grows large, run the `wp-workflow archive-plan`
  entry point to compress it.

